 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Senior Lithography Process TD Engineer Intel Albuquerque, NM 87114 Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Job Description 
Intel's Optane Group is hiring an experienced Process TD Engineer in the area of Photolithography to develop world class semiconductor manufacturing processes. 
You will have a successful track record of delivering leading edge process capability, in terms of yield, cost and manufacturability. This will involve exceptional collaboration with cross-functional/cross-company teams and tool vendors to meet device requirements for next-generation memory products. (Note: This is not a manufacturing position, this is a technology development position) 
Job Responsibilities Include: 
Design and optimization of lithography imaging processes for leading edge memory technology 
Demonstrate an in-depth knowledge of Lithography patterning techniques, including but not limited to, resist and stack evaluation, OPC model building, reticle technology, overlay and CD metrology 
Selecting and characterizing materials and equipment for the process to meet quality, reliability, cost, yield, productivity, and manufacturability requirements 
Creating innovative techniques using existing equipment, to improve current performance 
DOEs for both process and equipment TD 
Exceptional collaboration with cross-functional/cross-company teams and tool vendors to meet challenging program goals 
Working effectively with the equipment supplier to identify shortcomings, propose and evaluate hardware modification to mitigate issues 
Driving improvements on quality, reliability, cost, yield, process stability/capability, productivity and safety over variables such as materials, methods, and equipment 
Developing solutions utilizing model-based problem solving skills 
Transferring processes to low- and high volume manufacturing and providing support in new factory startup 
Training receiving process and equipment engineers in high volume factories 
Domestic and International travel, as necessary to support job responsibilities 
Identify potential intellectual properties (IP) opportunities and file disclosures 
Soft Skills: 
A fast learner, willing to adapt to the culture and the technology 
A person who thrives working in a dynamic environment 
Willing to be flexible in accommodating changing priorities and working hours to support business needs 
Qualifications 
Education: 
The candidate must have a PhD in Electrical Engineering, Chemical Engineering, Material Science, Physics, Chemistry or related field. 
Minimum Qualifications: 
5+ years of experience in the following areas: 
Semiconductor process and/or equipment development 
Photolithography and mask processes 
Lithography mask inspection tools 
Additional Qualifications: 
4+ years of experience in the following areas: 
Lithography links (scanners and tracks) and overlay metrology tools 
Semiconductor processing preferably in Memory process development for leading edge technology 
Technical problem-solving, multitasking, and analytical thinking 
Working with external and internal partners, including leading edge semiconductor equipment and/or materials manufacturers 
Inside this Business Group 
The Data Center Group (DCG) is at the heart of Intel’s transformation from a PC company to a company that runs the cloud and billions of smart, connected computing devices. The data center is the underpinning for every data-driven service, from artificial intelligence to 5G to high-performance computing, and DCG delivers the products and technologies—spanning software, processors, storage, I/O, and networking solutions—that fuel cloud, communications, enterprise, and government data centers around the world. 
